Spark structured Streaming + AUTOLOADER 
Main point tonote is in spark strcutured streaming we has the "checkpoint location" and in Autoloader we have additiobal "Schema Location".
It will automatially manages it , the main purposse of checkpoint is "IDENPOTENCY", which is exactly once.

What is the schema changes form source, that is where schema location comes in? 
  Schema once stored in Schema location, it will be cached as well and provides the info to autoloader, when new schema changes it goes to autoloader thinking that no schema changed but autoloader throws an error with UNKOWNFIELDEXCEPTION , then you dont have to change anything just rerun the code then the cached schema and schema is changed.
Even before the stream throws the error ,Autoloader performs schema inference on the latest micro-batch of the data and updates the schema location with the latest schema by mergng new columns to the end of the schema. The data types of existing columns remain unchanged.
